#text=My boyfriend 's birthday was just around the corner so I decided to bake a two-layer Strawberry Cake for him .
#text=To bake the cake , I needed sugar , milk , strawberry jello , vanilla extract , cake flour , butter , and strawberry puree .
#text=For the icing , I needed cream cheese , confectioner 's sugar , butter , and fresh strawberries .
#text=While the oven preheated , I mixed all of the dry ingredients in one bowl and all of the wet ingredients into another bowl .
#text=I then added the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stirred until everything was mixed well together .
#text=Once this was done , I poured the batter into two separate round cake pans and put the pans in the oven to bake for about 20 minutes .
#text=After I took the finished cakes out and placed them on wire racks to cool for about 10 minutes , I went ahead and made the frosting .
#text=Using an electric mixer , I beat the cream cheese and butter until they were creamy and then beat in the sugar and fresh strawberries until I got the smooth consistency that I wanted .
#text=Lastly , I assembled the cake by frosting the first layer then adding the second layer and frosting that as well .
#text=I also garnished the finished cake with some leftover strawberries I had .
